It was a missing person case that gripped the nation. Nicola Bulley, the 45-year-old mortgage adviser with two children, vanished seemingly into thin air while walking her dog. But this week, her family is facing their worst nightmare after her body was discovered in the River Wyre, near where she went missing. Here, Express.co.uk offers readers a chance to light a virtual candle and leave a message in tribute to her life. In a statement from Nicola's family, read by Lancashire police after her body had been identified, they paid tribute to "the one who made our lives so special". They said they would "never be able to comprehend what Nikki had gone through in her last moments and that will never leave us", but added: "We will never forget Nikki, how could we, she was the centre of our world, she was the one who made our lives so special and nothing will cast a shadow over that. "Our girls will get the support they need from the people who love them the most." 